ckages." Graduates are now "products" and "competing in the global economy" has replaced the search for truth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAcademic freedomxCanada. 0aAcademic freedomzCanada. 0aBusiness and educationxCanada. 0aBusiness and educationzCanada. 0aHigher education and statexCanada. 0aHigher education and statezCanada. 0aUniversity autonomyxCanada. 0aUniversity autonomyzCanada. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357688940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773576889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773576889/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles